@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<div style="color: white">
<body>
    <p> Aurora Auto, we respect and are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website, purchase our products, or interact with us in any other way. By using our services, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.</p>

    <h1>1. Information We Collect</h1>
    <br />

    <p>We collect both personal and non-personal information when you interact with us. This may include:</p> 
    <br />

    <h2>Personal Information:</h2>
    <br />

    <p>Contact Information: Name, email address, phone number, billing address, and shipping address.</p>
    <br />
    <p>Payment Information: Credit card details, billing address, and other payment-related data (Note: Payment processing is handled by secure third-party providers, and we do not store your full payment information).</p>
    <br />
    <p>Account Information: Username, password, and preferences if you create an account on our website.</p>
    <br />
    <p>Customer Support Information: Information you provide when contacting us for customer service, including correspondence history.</p>
    <br />
    

    <h2>Non-Personal Information:</h2>
    <br />

    <p>Usage Data: Information about how you access and use our website, such as IP address, browser type, operating system, pages visited, and time spent on each page.</p>
    <br />
    <p>Cookies and Tracking Technologies: We use cookies, web beacons, and other tracking technologies to enhance your browsing experience and improve our website’s functionality. You can manage cookies through your browser settings.</p>
    <br />


    <h1>2. How We Use Your Information</h1>
    <br />

    <p>We use the information we collect for various purposes, including:</p>
    <br />

    <p>Order Fulfillment: To process and deliver your orders, manage payments, and provide customer support.</p>
    <br />

    <p>Personalization: To tailor your experience, recommend products, and improve our website's content and functionality.</p>
    <br />

    <p>Communication: To send order confirmations, shipping notifications, and promotional materials (if you opt-in). You may opt-out of marketing communications at any time.</p>
    <br />

    <p>Customer Support: To respond to inquiries and resolve issues related to your purchases or experience with our products.</p>
    <br />

    <p>Improvement and Analytics: To analyze website usage, improve our products, services, and marketing efforts, and enhance your browsing experience.</p>
    <br />

    <p>Compliance: To comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our terms and conditions.</p>
    <br />

    <h1>3. How We Share Your Information</h1>
    <br />

    <p>We respect your privacy and will not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. However, we may share your information in the following circumstances:</p>
    <br />

    <p>Service Providers: We may share your information with third-party vendors who assist us in running our business, such as payment processors, shipping companies, and customer support services.</p>
    <br />

    <p> Legal Compliance: We may disclose your information to comply with applicable laws, regulations, or legal processes (e.g., subpoenas or court orders).</p>
    <br />

    <p>Business Transfers: In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred as part of the transaction, but we will notify you before your information is transferred to another entity.</p>
    <br />

    <h1>4. Data Security</h1>
    <br />

    <p> We take the security of your personal information seriously. We implement industry-standard security measures, including encryption and firewalls, to protect your data from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, please be aware that no method of data transmission over the internet is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information.</p>
    <br />

    <h1>5. Your Choices and Rights</h1>
    <br />

    <p>You have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p>
    <br />

    <p> Access and Correction: You may request access to the personal information we hold about you and request corrections if it is inaccurate or incomplete.</p>
    <br />

    <p>Opt-Out: You can unsubscribe from marketing emails at any time by clicking the "unsubscribe" link in the email or contacting us directly.</p>
    <br />

    <p>Delete or Deactivate Your Account: You may request to delete or deactivate your account, although some data may be retained for legal or administrative purposes.</p>
    <br />

    <p>Cookies: You can manage your cookie preferences through your browser settings. Please note that disabling certain cookies may affect the functionality of our website.</p>
    <br />

    <h1>6. Children's Privacy</h1>
    <br />

    <p>Aurora Auto does not knowingly collect personal information from individuals under the age of 13. If we become aware that a child has provided us with personal information, we will take steps to delete such information as quickly as possible. If you believe we have collected information from a child under the age of 13, please contact us immediately.</p>
    <br />

    <h1>7. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h1>
    <br />

    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make changes, we will post the updated policy on our website with the new effective date. We encourage you to review this policy periodically to stay informed about how we are protecting your information.</p>
    <br />

    <p> By using our website or purchasing products from Aurora Auto, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy.</p>
</body>
</div>
